                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6363 ST 2/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-04T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 4, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Foreign Minister stated to me this afternoon: “We had to drive the Standard
                    Oil Company out of Bolivia for political reasons. It will never be allowed to
                    return”. This confirms last sentence my telegram No. 26.<note n="37"
                        xml:id="d301fn37">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
